## feat(actions): build_action_service factory + GraphQL route wiring + integration test

### Context
Task 11 of the kinetic-action-layer plan. Wires the previously-built
`back.objects.actions` package into the running app so that:
- `build_action_service` is a single importable entry-point that ensures the
  kinetic Lakebase tables exist (once per process) and returns a ready
  `ActionService`.
- The GraphQL POST/GET routes optionally include a Mutation type (with
  `flagCustomerHighRisk`) when Lakebase is available, using the shared
  registry pool for the Lakebase connection.
- An env-gated integration test validates the full propose→approve→read-back
  loop against a live Lakebase instance.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/objects/actions/__init__.py`**
   - Added `build_action_service(connect)` factory function with
     process-wide `_schema_ready` guard.
   - Imports `back.objects.actions.types` on module load to trigger
     side-effect registration of action types in `default_registry`.

2. **`src/back/fastapi/graphql_routes.py`**
   - Added `_build_action_connect(settings)` helper that returns the
     shared `_LakebasePool.connection` for the registry schema.
   - Updated `_get_schema_and_context` to accept an optional `request`
     kwarg; when provided and Lakebase is available it builds
     `service_factory` and `ctx_factory` and passes them to
     `_default_builder.build_for_domain(...)`.
   - Actor email extracted from `request.state.user_email` (set by
     `PermissionMiddleware`) falling back to `x-forwarded-email` header.
   - Updated `graphql_playground` and `graphql_execute` route handlers
     to pass `request=request`; `graphql_execute` gains a `request:
     Request` parameter.
   - `graphql_sdl` and `graphql_debug` stay query-only (no mutation).

3. **`tests/units/actions/test_build_service.py`** *(new)*
   - Unit test for `build_action_service`; resets `_schema_ready` flag
     before each call to ensure DDL always runs.

4. **`tests/integration/__init__.py`** *(new)*
5. **`tests/integration/actions/__init__.py`** *(new)*
6. **`tests/integration/actions/conftest.py`** *(new)*
   - `test_connect` backed by `_get_pool(auth, schema, database).connection`
     — same pool the registry store uses.
7. **`tests/integration/actions/test_action_loop_lakebase.py`** *(new)*
   - Full propose→approve→read-back integration test; skipped unless
     `LAKEBASE_TEST_CONNECT=1` is set.

### Modified files
- `src/back/objects/actions/__init__.py`
- `src/back/fastapi/graphql_routes.py`
- `tests/units/actions/test_build_service.py` (new)
- `tests/integration/__init__.py` (new)
- `tests/integration/actions/__init__.py` (new)
- `tests/integration/actions/conftest.py` (new)
- `tests/integration/actions/test_action_loop_lakebase.py` (new)

### Test results
- `tests/units/actions/test_build_service.py` — 1 passed
- `tests/integration/actions/` — 1 skipped (env gate working)
- `tests/units -k "graphql or fastapi or route"` — 167 passed, 1 skipped
- `tests/units` (full) — 2081 passed, 12 skipped, 2 pre-existing failures
  in `test_external_api.py::TestDomainVersions` (registry not configured
  in offline env — confirmed pre-existing, not introduced by this task)

